-- Copper Increases for Sixth Day in New York on Declining Global Stockpiles
-- Wendy Pugh
-- 2010-07-25T22:14:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-25/copper-increases-for-sixth-day-in-new-york-on-declining-global-stockpiles.html

          
          
             Copper futures in New York advanced
for a sixth day after inventories dropped last week. The metal
rallied 0.3 percent to $3.1930 a pound at 8:07 a.m. Melbourne
time.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
